Accesibility
1. use HTML sementics, they readable by screen reader
2. a. test webpage in gray scale, for color blind users. make sure all text and border has enough color contrast
   b. don't always depends on color like for showing error in red, also show an error icon.
   c. use color contrast checker
3. use aria attributes - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/ARIA_Techniques
	a. role
	b. aria-label

